JOHANNESBURG - Old Mutual has announced that the former CEO of Alexander Forbes, Peter Moyo, is to take the helm from 11 June. Moyo takes over from Bruce Hemphill, who will step down on the same day. READ: Old Mutual profits up by 22% in 2017 Hemphill has over the past few months overseen Old Mutual’s "managed separation", whereby its UK arm will be unbundled to list on the London Stock Exchange under a new name, Quilter. The company’s remaining Africa-focused segment will keep its listing on the JSE, trading under a new stock name, O-M-L, from 26 June. eNCA